track_notes:
Proceed on 181A to a forest service sign that says dead end/administrative use only/no motorized vehicles. Park here. There is a locked gate 1/4 mile from this sign. Hike on the road past the locked gate. For about a mile and then leave the road and bushwhack about 1.5 miles to the summit. This is a wonderful hike of moderate difficulty. Though a large aspen grove extends to the summit, there are several large, open, grassy knolls on the way up that provide excellent views of the Arkansas Valley and Collegiate Peaks. Highly recommended. There is a summit register at the top that showed two summits in 2015.

Note: The road designations on Google Maps are incorrect as of 20150907. Roads 180 and 181 are incorrectly shown as 181A and the actual 181A is not shown. However, these roads do have Forest Service road signs designating the correct road number. You can also refer to these coordinates:
Turn off for 181: 38.601111, -105.942199
Turn off for 181A:38.582228, -1
